n\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"latency_spike\", \"checkoutservice->cartservice\", \"checkoutservice->shippingservice\", \"frontend->checkoutservice\", \"frontend->recommendationservice\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Significant delay observed with latency increase (up to ~60 times higher).\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"operation_name\": \"hipstershop.CheckoutService/PlaceOrder\",\n        \"normal_avg_duration\": 144331.801 ms,\n        \"anomaly_avg_duration\": 8610403.303 ms,\n        \"anomaly_count\": 22\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Dependency delay affecting quick responses to checkout.\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"operation_name\": \"hipstershop.CartService/GetCart\",\n        \"normal_avg_duration\": 2462.712 ms,\n        \"anomaly_avg_duration\": 12073.424 ms,\n        \"anomaly_count\": 2\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"redis\",\n      \"reason\": \"Redis heavy tasks influencing processing linked calls.\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"operation_name\": \"HGET\",\n        \"normal_avg_duration (Redis cart)\": \"1738-user'd432–EXHING long ms tasksDaemon requests ports.activ.red.aps.ctrl Normal\",\n }\n(>>)", "metric_analysis_findings": "Based on the anomaly metrics data received for the event, I'll proceed to identify significant abnormal patterns and root causes.\n\n### Analysis Process:\n1. Review `anomaly_metrics` to identify top abnormal indicators with significant `median_change_ratio` or `p99_change_ratio`.\n2. Correlate anomalies across `Node`, `Pod`, and `Service` levels using the provided `node_pod_mapping`.\n3. Prioritize `Node` issues over `Pod` and `Service` issues.\n\n### Findings:\n\n1. **Node-Level Anomalies**:\n    - **aiops-k8s-08** experienced a significant drop in `node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes`, from 9354969088 bytes to 6169513984 bytes (change ratio: 0.4104). This points to high memory exhaustion on this node.\n\n2. **Pod-Level Anomalies**:\n    - The Pod `redis-cart-0` running on `aiops-k8s-08` exhibited abnormal behavior with `pod_cpu_usage` change ratio of `2.0`. This is likely a symptom of node resource issues, as multiple Pods on the same node showed degradation.\n\n3. **Service-Level Anomalies**:\n    - `currencyservice` and `frontend` services showed abnormal increases in response time `rrt_max`. \n      - `currencyservice-2` reported an increase in `rrt_max` from 2386ms to 1071647ms (change ratio: 1.9911).\n      - `frontend-0` experienced an increase in `rrt_max` from 207531 to 9020331ms (change ratio: 1.91). Both correlate with resource contention on Node `aiops-k8s-08`.\n\n### Root Cause:\nThe root cause appears to be resource exhaustion on the node `aiops-k8s-08`, specifically `node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes`. This led to cascading performance degradation on Pods (`redis-cart-0`) and services (`currencyservice` and `frontend`) hosted on the same node.\n\n### Output (JSON):\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes\", \"pod_cpu_usage\", \"rrt_max\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-08\",\n      \"reason\": \"High memory exhaustion (`node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes` dropped by 41%) caused resource contention and subsequent degradation of multiple services hosted on the node.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Node memory availability dropped from 9354969088 to 6169513984 bytes (41% decrease). Cascading effects observed in service-level `rrt_max` and pod-level CPU usage.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"}
